Sentencas: The optimal anode mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta (LSCM) and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (GDC) is evaluated in this study.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anodes with GDC share of 30-100 wt.% are investigated.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Initial polarization resistance decreased as the GDC share increased.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, anodes with GDC share over 80 wt.% significantly deteriorated in the degradation tests.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Nano-scale cracks were observed in the GDC phase at the grain boundaries after the test.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These nano-cracks were not observed in composite anodes, from which it is implied that LSCM has stabilization effect on GDC structure.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The mass fraction of LSCM : GDC = 30 : 70 wt.% is found to be optimal in terms of initial electrochemical performance and stability.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The optimal LSCM-GDC shows lower polarization resistance than conventional Ni-YSZ at low temperatures, which is comparable to Ni-GDC anode.
Titulo: Effects of mass fraction of La0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ composite anodes for nickel free solid oxide fuel cells
